Automate a Task Using a Bash Script Create a Bash script using nano myscript.sh, then add the following code: #!/bin/bash; echo "Hello, $(whoami)! The current date and time is: $(date)". Save the file, make it executable with chmod +x myscript.sh, and run it using ./myscript.sh. Modify the script to also display system uptime and disk space usage. Task: Submit the updated script and execution screenshot. 

